nsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533135\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vqq1665702865300.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vqq1665702865300.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vqq1665702865300.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vqq1665702865300\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Using Web Server Authentication\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">If <code class=\"ph codeph\">AUTHORIZATION=REMOTE_USER</code>, the web server needs to perform the authentication, and anonymous is not allowed. You need to configure the web server to perform the authentication, and you can access the user logon information with <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$user</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$password</span>.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"vqq1665702865300__context_w1214ab1b5b1_w1215ab1b5_w1216ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"vqq1665702865300__topic_d22598e1_d22599e1_d22600e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vqq1665702865300__p_d22601e1_d22602e1_d22603e1\">The following steps show how to configure Tomcat BASIC authentication and the Uniface servlet so that a logon box is displayed for each first access of the web application by a particular user.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vqq1665702865300__p_d22604e1_d22605e1_d22606e1\">If you use a web server other than Tomcat, you can replace the steps 1 and 2 with the configuration of your web server.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vqq1665702865300__p_d22607e1_d22608e1_d22609e1\">To use Tomcat BASIC authentication:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vqq1665702865300__li_d11060e1_d11061e1_d11062e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Edit the file <span class=\"ph filepath\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">UnifaceAPSInstallDir</var>/common/tomcat/conf/tomcat-users.xml</span> to add your users, passwords and roles.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vqq1665702865300__li_d11063e1_d11064e1_d11065e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Add the security constraint to the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yda1665702742322.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yda1665702742322.html\" title=\"Configuration file of the web application.\">web.xml</a> file, for example:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">&lt;web-app&gt;\n … …\n&lt;security-constraint&gt; \n &lt;web-resource-collection&gt; \n &lt;web-resource-name&gt;The Entire Web Application&lt;/web-resource-name&gt; \n &lt;url-pattern&gt;/*&lt;/url-pattern&gt; \n &lt;/web-resource-collection&gt; \n &lt;auth-constraint&gt; \n &lt;role-name&gt;tomcat&lt;/role-name&gt; \n &lt;/auth-constraint&gt; \n&lt;/security-constraint&gt; \n&lt;login-config&gt; \n &lt;auth-method&gt;BASIC&lt;/auth-method&gt; \n &lt;realm-name&gt;Tomcat Supported Realm&lt;/realm-name&gt; \n&lt;/login-config&gt; \n&lt;security-role&gt; \n &lt;description&gt;An example role defined in \"conf/tomcat-users.xml\"\n &lt;/description&gt; \n &lt;role-name&gt;tomcat&lt;/role-name&gt; \n&lt;/security-role&gt;\n&lt;/web-app&gt;\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vqq1665702865300__li_d11066e1_d11067e1_d11068e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the same <span class=\"ph filepath\">web.xml</span> file, under the servlet <code class=\"ph codeph\">wrd</code> specification, set <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">AUTHORIZATION</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">REMOTE_USER</code>:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">&lt;servlet&gt; \n &lt;servlet-name&gt; \n wrd\n… …\n &lt;init-param&gt; \n &lt;param-name&gt;AUTHORIZATION&lt;/param-name&gt; \n &lt;param-value&gt;REMOTE_USER&lt;/param-value&gt;\n &lt;/init-param&gt;\n&lt;/servlet&gt;\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/noh1665702742459.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>AUTHORIZATION</a><p>Instructs the WRD that user authorization is required. If not specified, the web server determines whether, and what kind of, user authorization is performed.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533135\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533135\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Using Web Server Authentication Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Using Web Server Authentication If AUTHORIZATION=REMOTE_USER , the web server needs to perform the authentication, and anonymous is not allowed. You need to configure the web server to perform the authentication, and you can access the user logon information with $user and $password . The following steps show how to configure Tomcat BASIC authentication and the Uniface servlet so that a logon box is displayed for each first access of the web application by a particular user. If you use a web server other than Tomcat, you can replace the steps 1 and 2 with the configuration of your web server. To use Tomcat BASIC authentication: Edit the file UnifaceAPSInstallDir /common/tomcat/conf/tomcat-users.xml to add your users, passwords and roles. Add the security constraint to the web.xml file, for example: <web-app> … … <security-constraint> <web-resource-collection> <web-resource-name>The Entire Web Application</web-resource-name> <url-pattern>/*</url-pattern> </web-resource-collection> <auth-constraint> <role-name>tomcat</role-name> </auth-constraint> </security-constraint> <login-config> <auth-method>BASIC</auth-method> <realm-name>Tomcat Supported Realm</realm-name> </login-config> <security-role> <description>An example role defined in \"conf/tomcat-users.xml\" </description> <role-name>tomcat</role-name> </security-role> </web-app> Copy In the same web.xml file, under the servlet wrd specification, set AUTHORIZATION to REMOTE_USER : <servlet> <servlet-name> wrd … … <init-param> <param-name>AUTHORIZATION</param-name> <param-value>REMOTE_USER</param-value> </init-param> </servlet> Copy Related Links AUTHORIZATION Instructs the WRD that user authorization is required. If not specified, the web server determines whether, and what kind of, user authorization is performed. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}